title: Chemical fibers global production 2000 to 2018
summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 3 different Fiber Types for 10 groups 2000, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, and 2018 that are presented on the X-axis.
In Fiber Type Total, 2018 had the highest SOME LABEL 73400.0 among the 10 groups and in Cellulose fibers, 2000 had the lowest SOME LABEL 2640.0.
In Fiber Type Total, 2013 had the maximum SOME LABEL and it saw the lowest in Fiber Type Cellulose fibers out of all 3 Fiber Types.
Fiber Type Total and Cellulose fibers had the biggest gap of 54400.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for 2013.
min_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 3 different Fiber Types on X-axis for 10 groups 2000, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, and 2018. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
In Fiber Type Total, 2018 had the highest SOME LABEL 73400.0 among the 10 groups and in Cellulose fibers, 2000 had the lowest SOME LABEL 2640.0.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 3 different Fiber Types for 10 groups 2000, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, and 2018 that are presented on the X-axis.
Out of all 10 groups, 2018 had the highest SOME LABEL in Fiber Type Total and 2000 had the lowest SOME LABEL in Fiber Type Cellulose fibers.
In Fiber Type Total, 2013 had the highest SOME LABEL among all 3 Fiber Types and it has the lowest SOME LABEL in Fiber Type Cellulose fibers.
Fiber Type Total and Cellulose fibers had the biggest gap of 54400.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for 2013.
Among all 10 groups, 2017 had the gap of 64900.0 between the maximum and minimum SOME LABEL observed in Fiber Type Total and Cellulose fibers respectively.
2018 had the maximum SOME LABEL out of all 10 groups in Fiber Type Total followed by 2018 in Total, and the minimum SOME LABEL is found for 2000 in Cellulose fibers.

On average, the Fiber Type Total had the highest SOME LABEL for all 10 groups 2000, 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016, 2017, and 2018. Whereas Cellulose fibers had the lowest average SOME LABEL.
